1
00:00:02,468 --> 00:00:04,969
[ Ukulele strumming ]

2
00:00:23,255 --> 00:00:25,423
Bachelorette party!
All right!

3
00:00:25,425 --> 00:00:29,260
Going to the strip club.
All right. Going to Pickles.

4
00:00:29,262 --> 00:00:33,097
Boy, am I gonna need some
quarters tonight.
[ Laughs ]

5
00:00:33,099 --> 00:00:33,831
Quarters?
Yeah.

6
00:00:33,833 --> 00:00:36,267
Mm-hmm.
What are you gonna
do with quarters, Lin?

7
00:00:36,269 --> 00:00:38,202
Oh, I'll plop 'em
in their G-strings.

8
00:00:38,204 --> 00:00:41,139
You'll-- [ Scoffs ] You'll plop
quarters in their G-strings?

9
00:00:41,141 --> 00:00:43,341
Plop 'em right in.
Plippity plop.

10
00:00:43,343 --> 00:00:44,642
- At Pickles?
- Pickles.

11
00:00:44,644 --> 00:00:45,810
Why do they call it Pickles?

12
00:00:45,812 --> 00:00:47,445
They actually serve pickles.
Mmm.

13
00:00:47,447 --> 00:00:49,847
No, I'm not kidding.
They really have good pickles.

14
00:00:49,849 --> 00:00:52,083
You'd think they wouldn't,
but they're delicious.

15
00:00:52,085 --> 00:00:53,718
You're going to dinner theater,
aren't you?

16
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:55,153
Nah--
[ Nervous Laughing ]

17
00:00:55,155 --> 00:00:57,422
Wha--
What do you mean?

18
00:00:57,424 --> 00:00:59,490
Wait-- That is crazy.

19
00:00:59,492 --> 00:01:00,425
Fine, Bob.
You got me.

20
00:01:00,427 --> 00:01:02,727
I know you don't approve
of dinner theater,
so I fibbed.

21
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:04,762
You know what? I'd rather
you go to a strip club.

22
00:01:04,764 --> 00:01:06,898
What do you have against
dinner theater, Dad?

23
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:09,834
Well, first of all, Gene,
it's neither dinner nor theater.

24
00:01:09,836 --> 00:01:13,171
It's like the imitation
cheese of theater.

25
00:01:13,173 --> 00:01:13,738
Sounds fun.

26
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:15,606
Imitation cheese
is delicious.

27
00:01:15,608 --> 00:01:17,308
That's my boy.
That's my star.

28
00:01:17,310 --> 00:01:19,277
Linda, you know what
the real problem is?
What?

29
00:01:19,279 --> 00:01:22,880
It's the result
of dinner theater--
what it does to you.

30
00:01:22,882 --> 00:01:24,215
Makes you sing everything.

31
00:01:24,217 --> 00:01:27,185
Who was that?
♪ Wrong number

32
00:01:27,187 --> 00:01:28,619
- [ Groans ]
- ♪ Yeah

33
00:01:28,621 --> 00:01:30,288
So what's for breakfast?

34
00:01:30,290 --> 00:01:31,389
♪ Eggs, eggs

35
00:01:31,391 --> 00:01:34,459
♪ Eggs, bom-bom
Eggs, eggs, eggs, eggs ♪

36
00:01:34,461 --> 00:01:36,327
Oh, my God.
♪ Bom-bomp

37
00:01:36,329 --> 00:01:40,264
So, Lin, it's, uh--
All right.

38
00:01:40,266 --> 00:01:42,700
♪ Not tonight
No ♪

39
00:01:42,702 --> 00:01:43,501
Okay.

40
00:01:43,503 --> 00:01:45,903
♪ Not tonight
No ♪

41
00:01:45,905 --> 00:01:46,504
I get it!

42
00:01:46,506 --> 00:01:49,240
And so you're gonna be doing
that all week, right?

43
00:01:49,242 --> 00:01:54,378
♪ No
[ Holds Note ]

44
00:01:54,380 --> 00:01:55,847
♪ Yeah

45
00:01:55,849 --> 00:01:56,514
[ Laughs ]

46
00:01:56,516 --> 00:01:59,851
[ Man ]
♪ We drink, we loot,
we rape, we shoot ♪

47
00:01:59,853 --> 00:02:03,754
[ Man #2 ]
♪ We sing, we dance,
we twirl, we prance ♪

48
00:02:03,756 --> 00:02:11,429
[ With Singers ]
♪ We're the Pirates
of Panache ♪

49
00:02:11,431 --> 00:02:14,332
Ow. Ow. Ow.
Linda,
tell me everything.

50
00:02:14,334 --> 00:02:17,835
Oh, Mort, I'm telling you,
to be in dinner theater--

51
00:02:17,837 --> 00:02:20,471
If I could do my life
over again, if I could--

52
00:02:20,473 --> 00:02:22,740
[ Groans ]
If I could just have
one chance--

53
00:02:22,742 --> 00:02:24,408
[ Laughs ]
You'd do that?
Yeah.

54
00:02:24,410 --> 00:02:26,911
Linda, what are you
talking about?
You've got a great life.

55
00:02:26,913 --> 00:02:28,412
You work in a restaurant.

56
00:02:28,414 --> 00:02:30,581
- You get to feed
the world, right?
- Right.

57
00:02:30,583 --> 00:02:33,384
There was someone in here from
Canada last week. Remember?

58
00:02:33,386 --> 00:02:36,387
And we learned
all about that country.
That's great.

59
00:02:36,389 --> 00:02:37,255
I hate that country.

60
00:02:37,257 --> 00:02:42,293
You know, Linda, you've got
the dinner part already.
You know what that means.

61
00:02:42,295 --> 00:02:44,695
You're halfway to doing--

62
00:02:44,697 --> 00:02:46,330
- Yeah?
- Your own--

63
00:02:46,332 --> 00:02:48,399
Say it. Yeah. Say it.
What? What?

64
00:02:48,401 --> 00:02:50,735
Dinner theater!
Your very own
dinner theater!

65
00:02:50,737 --> 00:02:52,370
- Dinner theater. Yes!
- No--

66
00:02:52,372 --> 00:02:54,372
Yeah! My own din--
[ Laughs ]
Yay!

67
00:02:54,374 --> 00:02:57,675
- Why are we excited?
- Hamburger dinner theater?

68
00:02:57,677 --> 00:02:58,876
Ah, come on, Bobby!

69
00:02:58,878 --> 00:03:02,313
We work hard every day
to make your dream come true.

70
00:03:02,315 --> 00:03:03,781
Why can't we
do my dream too?

71
00:03:03,783 --> 00:03:07,618
About how long do you think
your dream will take?
Like an hour, hour and a half?

72
00:03:07,620 --> 00:03:11,422
Are you crazy?
It's got to be at least
a three-week engagement.

73
00:03:11,424 --> 00:03:13,558
Three weeks?
How about three days?

74
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:15,793
All right.
We'll take it.
[ Chuckles ]

75
00:03:15,795 --> 00:03:17,695
This is gonna be wonderful!

76
00:03:17,697 --> 00:03:18,896
What's the show
gonna be?

77
00:03:18,898 --> 00:03:21,766
[ Sighs ]
Murder. Murder mystery.

78
00:03:21,768 --> 00:03:25,303
- [ Scoffs ]
- How about
mass murder mystery?

79
00:03:25,305 --> 00:03:25,970
Okay, sure.

80
00:03:25,972 --> 00:03:27,672
And a musical?
Of course.

81
00:03:27,674 --> 00:03:29,006
Can it also be a love story?

82
00:03:29,008 --> 00:03:36,314
Aw! A mass murder
mystery musical
love story set in, uh--

83
00:03:36,316 --> 00:03:39,417
Nazi Germany.
Oh! In Montreal.

84
00:03:39,419 --> 00:03:40,551
Enough with Canada!

85
00:03:40,553 --> 00:03:44,989
In a ketchup factory?
A sexy ketchup factory?

86
00:03:45,691 --> 00:03:47,592
[ Air Squeezing ]

87
00:03:47,594 --> 00:03:50,928
I got it!
In a morgue!
I have props.

88
00:03:50,930 --> 00:03:53,397
Oh, come on.
Yes, yes!
Mort, that's it.

89
00:03:53,399 --> 00:03:56,033
We'll call it Dreamatorium.
Really?

90
00:03:56,035 --> 00:03:58,436
♪ Dreamatorium

91
00:03:58,438 --> 00:04:01,005
♪ It's a Dreamatorium

92
00:04:01,007 --> 00:04:03,708
[ Groans ]
♪ Bom-bomp

93
00:04:05,744 --> 00:04:08,546
Look at this set.
Am I in a morgue?

94
00:04:08,548 --> 00:04:09,380
Oh, it feels like I am.

95
00:04:09,382 --> 00:04:13,050
I am just so happy
we've all been bitten by
the dinner theater bug.

96
00:04:13,052 --> 00:04:16,821
Now, Gene, you're on
sound effects, naturally.

97
00:04:16,823 --> 00:04:18,489
[ Man Screams ]

98
00:04:18,491 --> 00:04:19,457
Ominous.

99
00:04:19,459 --> 00:04:20,424
Chills. Oh!

100
00:04:20,426 --> 00:04:23,961
Remember-- every character
gets some intro and outro music.

101
00:04:23,963 --> 00:04:27,064
- You got it.
- ♪ [ Bouncy Theme ]

102
00:04:27,066 --> 00:04:30,601
- Don't. Don't score me.
- [ Deflating Sound ]

103
00:04:30,603 --> 00:04:32,903
Mort, you're
on visual effects.

104
00:04:32,905 --> 00:04:35,906
Fake blood. Or is it?

105
00:04:35,908 --> 00:04:36,507
Now, script.

106
00:04:36,509 --> 00:04:39,977
As you know,
everyone who enters my morgue
is mysteriously killed.

107
00:04:39,979 --> 00:04:43,581
- Mort-- body delivery guy,
victim one.
- ♪ [ Single Note ]

108
00:04:43,583 --> 00:04:47,718
Gene-- flower delivery guy,
victim two.
♪ [ Higher Note ]

109
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:50,988
Tina-- tree,
victim three.
♪ [ Lower Note ]

110
00:04:50,990 --> 00:04:54,825
Louise-- the butler
who everyone thinks
is the killer.

111
00:04:54,827 --> 00:04:57,561
You're the red herring.
♪ [ Suspense Note ]

112
00:04:57,563 --> 00:04:59,096
Tina's a tree
that gets killed?

113
00:04:59,098 --> 00:05:03,434
She wants to be a tree,
she can be a tree.
Tina's got stage fright.

114
00:05:03,436 --> 00:05:04,035
I have stage fright?

115
00:05:04,037 --> 00:05:07,972
Yes, sweetie. Ever since
you were a little baby.

116
00:05:07,974 --> 00:05:11,375
Tina, say "Mommy."
"Mommy."

117
00:05:11,377 --> 00:05:12,777
Uh--
"Ma."

118
00:05:12,779 --> 00:05:13,811
Huh?
No.

119
00:05:13,813 --> 00:05:16,580
I'll keep cutting.
You say when.

120
00:05:16,582 --> 00:05:17,948
Uh--

121
00:05:17,950 --> 00:05:18,849
Uh-- Uh--

122
00:05:18,851 --> 00:05:21,385
[ Female Operator ]
911.
What's your emergency?

123
00:05:21,387 --> 00:05:22,353
Uh--

124
00:05:22,355 --> 00:05:24,889
Tina! Help!
Uh-- Uhh--

125
00:05:24,891 --> 00:05:27,425
Hello?
Tina! Fire!

126
00:05:27,427 --> 00:05:28,492
Uhh--

127
00:05:28,494 --> 00:05:29,126
That explains a lot.

128
00:05:29,128 --> 00:05:31,462
Now, Bobby, there's a small part
I'd like you to play--

129
00:05:31,464 --> 00:05:37,435
the tree surgeon, who tries
to save the tree but instead
becomes victim number four.

130
00:05:37,437 --> 00:05:38,936
I'd love to,
but absolutely not.

131
00:05:38,938 --> 00:05:42,440
I'm already doing
the dinner part of this
dinner theater, Lin--

132
00:05:42,442 --> 00:05:44,108
by myself, I might add.

133
00:05:44,110 --> 00:05:46,377
- It's one line!
- No.

134
00:05:46,379 --> 00:05:49,814
What's the matter?
Afraid you might get bitten?

135
00:05:49,816 --> 00:05:51,148
[ Buzzes ]
Gotcha!
[ Laughs ]

136
00:05:51,150 --> 00:05:54,418
Yeah. Yeah, good.
Let's do a scene right now.
Come on.

137
00:05:54,420 --> 00:05:56,387
Let's do an improv.
An improv?

138
00:05:56,389 --> 00:05:57,521
Yeah, an improv. I--

139
00:05:57,523 --> 00:06:01,792
Hi. What's your--
Hi. How are you?
I'm just standing out here.

140
00:06:01,794 --> 00:06:03,694
[ Mutters ]
So am I.

141
00:06:03,696 --> 00:06:05,830
It's cold out.

142
00:06:05,832 --> 00:06:07,431
Not really.

143
00:06:07,433 --> 00:06:10,000
Uh--
I have
a big coat on.

144
00:06:10,002 --> 00:06:11,102
See? You're good.
You're good.

145
00:06:11,104 --> 00:06:12,903
That was good. Yes!
I don't like it.
I don't like it.

146
00:06:12,905 --> 00:06:15,873
I don't like it.
That was a whole scene.
It just becomes a play.

147
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:17,775
I love that.
That's the play
we should do.

148
00:06:17,777 --> 00:06:20,478
We'll call it Big Coat.
[ Barking ]

149
00:06:22,414 --> 00:06:25,750
Red leather, yellow leather.
Red leather, yellow leather.

150
00:06:25,752 --> 00:06:27,151
Um, are you talking
to me?

151
00:06:27,153 --> 00:06:30,988
I'm warming up my instrument!
Unbelievable!

152
00:06:30,990 --> 00:06:32,890
I am sor--
Uhh--

153
00:06:32,892 --> 00:06:35,659
Hey, I'm sorry.
It's preshow nerves.

154
00:06:35,661 --> 00:06:36,761
Come here.
Hug for luck.

155
00:06:36,763 --> 00:06:40,965
You freakin' idiot!
You don't hug for luck
in the theater!

156
00:06:40,967 --> 00:06:42,933
Uhh--
Shh, shh, shh.
Shh-shh.

157
00:06:42,935 --> 00:06:44,034
I'm sorry, baby.
Shh, shh, shh.

158
00:06:44,036 --> 00:06:48,105
I didn't mean it, baby.
You know how I get
before a big show.

159
00:06:48,107 --> 00:06:50,007
You know how I get.

160
00:06:50,009 --> 00:06:51,542
Get off of me!
Uhh--

161
00:06:51,544 --> 00:06:53,010
You're smudging my makeup!
Uhh--

162
00:06:53,012 --> 00:06:55,613
You want me to go out there
in front of these people...

163
00:06:55,615 --> 00:06:58,816
with this makeup all smudged,
you clumsy oaf!

164
00:06:58,818 --> 00:07:01,786
[ Sighs ]
Sorry, baby.
Come here.

165
00:07:01,788 --> 00:07:05,156
♪ [ Bouncy ]

166
00:07:06,658 --> 00:07:08,659
[ Bell Dings ]
Good evening, ladies.

167
00:07:08,661 --> 00:07:10,961
Please enter and be 'tained.

168
00:07:10,963 --> 00:07:14,265
I don't get it, Bob.
Why are people buying tickets
to eat a burger?

169
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:15,666
Linda's putting on
a dinner theater,

170
00:07:15,668 --> 00:07:18,469
so you're paying
for the entertainment
plus the burger.

171
00:07:18,471 --> 00:07:19,770
What if someone only wants
to eat a hamburger?

172
00:07:19,772 --> 00:07:22,973
I guess you could just pay
for the burger and turn
your back to the stage.

173
00:07:22,975 --> 00:07:25,810
I could kind of watch
like this, you know,
with my peripheral vision.

174
00:07:25,812 --> 00:07:29,547
It'd be the honor system, Teddy.
I mean, if you find yourself
watching the show,

175
00:07:29,549 --> 00:07:31,182
you should probably
buy a ticket, right?

176
00:07:31,184 --> 00:07:32,583
[ Teddy ]
Oh, that's fair.
That's more than fair.

177
00:07:32,585 --> 00:07:35,252
- [ Bob ] But, Teddy, you can't
talk during the show.
- No. No. No, I get it.

178
00:07:35,254 --> 00:07:37,555
One time I was
at the movies, right?
♪ [ Fanfare ]

179
00:07:37,557 --> 00:07:39,056
- Teddy, shh!
- This guy's phone goes off--

180
00:07:39,058 --> 00:07:39,990
[ Bob ]
Teddy, they're starting.

181
00:07:39,992 --> 00:07:41,459
[ Whispering ]
And this guy's phone
goes off--

182
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:42,860
And he picks up
the phone--
Don't tell the story, Teddy.

183
00:07:42,862 --> 00:07:45,529
He picks up the phone, but
everyone in the theater's like--
Don't tell-- Shh!

184
00:07:45,531 --> 00:07:47,598
"Stop it!"
You know, just "stop," right?
Teddy, stop!

185
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,700
Stop telling the story.
He just--
And everyone is like,

186
00:07:49,702 --> 00:07:50,901
"Who's the killer?"
Shut your mouth.

187
00:07:50,903 --> 00:07:53,871
Right. No.
That's what that guy did.
Shut your mouth.

188
00:07:53,873 --> 00:07:56,106
[ Linda Clears Throat ]

189
00:07:56,208 --> 00:07:57,741
♪ Everything dies

190
00:07:57,743 --> 00:08:00,144
♪ But love
♪ [ Keyboard Continues ]

191
00:08:00,146 --> 00:08:01,078
Good evening.

192
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:01,946
This is the story of love,

193
00:08:01,948 --> 00:08:08,319
but there will be a murderer,
and it's up to you to guess
who that murderer is.

194
00:08:08,321 --> 00:08:11,789
Hint-- It's not me.

195
00:08:11,791 --> 00:08:14,892
Because I'm just Gladys,
a lonely morgue owner.

196
00:08:14,894 --> 00:08:18,896
You know, they say most people
find love where they work.

197
00:08:18,898 --> 00:08:20,965
Well, look where I work.

198
00:08:21,233 --> 00:08:25,002
Corpse delivery
for a lonely morgue owner.

199
00:08:25,004 --> 00:08:28,906
♪ That would be me

200
00:08:28,908 --> 00:08:31,942
[ Mort Screams ]

201
00:08:31,944 --> 00:08:34,979
I'm being murdered... to death!

202
00:08:34,981 --> 00:08:40,184
[ Screaming ]

203
00:08:40,952 --> 00:08:45,122
So no actual murder tonight,
just a lot of fake blood
and fake organs.

204
00:08:45,124 --> 00:08:47,758
[ Chuckles ]
Right. Right. Fake.
[ Radio Chatter ]

205
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:51,028
Yeah, we might have overdone it
a little on the gore.

206
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:51,962
Well, no harm done.

207
00:08:51,964 --> 00:08:53,764
Except for the people
being treated for shock.

208
00:08:53,766 --> 00:08:56,767
Yeah, and the people
who demanded their money back.

209
00:08:56,769 --> 00:08:57,134
Eh.

210
00:08:57,136 --> 00:08:59,770
Well, the next performance
is gonna be really great.

211
00:08:59,772 --> 00:09:03,307
Next performance?
Wasn't tonight's debacle
the end of dinner theater?

212
00:09:03,309 --> 00:09:06,277
I just need to tweak
some stuff for tomorrow's show.

213
00:09:06,279 --> 00:09:08,812
Maybe tone down
the blood a smidge.
What?

214
00:09:08,814 --> 00:09:12,349
I've been thinking.
I want to get over
the stage fright.

215
00:09:12,351 --> 00:09:13,951
I think I'd like
to have a line.

216
00:09:13,953 --> 00:09:17,621
Aw, Bob!
Our tree is growing up
and sprouting words.

217
00:09:17,623 --> 00:09:20,791
Let's write you a speech for
tomorrow night's performance.

218
00:09:20,793 --> 00:09:22,226
Can I say, "No. Don't"?

219
00:09:22,228 --> 00:09:25,195
That's exactly
what a tree would say!

220
00:09:25,197 --> 00:09:26,931
I'll have it memorized
by tomorrow night.

221
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:30,167
Lin, you lived out
your dream on stage
for a couple minutes,

222
00:09:30,169 --> 00:09:32,102
and since there were
no charges filed--

223
00:09:32,104 --> 00:09:34,104
They can never take that
away from you, right?

224
00:09:34,106 --> 00:09:37,708
Bob, my dream has not been--
♪ satisfied

225
00:09:37,710 --> 00:09:39,209
The show must go on, Dad.

226
00:09:39,211 --> 00:09:42,279
Yeah. Did you give up after
you made your first burger?

227
00:09:42,281 --> 00:09:44,782
It ain't over
till it's over.

228
00:09:44,784 --> 00:09:46,850
No. You added
garlic powder.

229
00:09:46,852 --> 00:09:50,988
Luck is 90%
preparation and--
Gene, enough.

230
00:09:50,990 --> 00:09:51,922
[ Gene Groans ]

231
00:09:51,924 --> 00:09:54,124
[ Sighs ]
Two more shows.

232
00:09:55,427 --> 00:09:58,329
This tastes nothing
like real blood!

233
00:09:59,831 --> 00:10:02,666
Flowers for a lonely
morgue owner.

234
00:10:02,668 --> 00:10:03,434
That's me!

235
00:10:03,436 --> 00:10:08,939
Oh, God! That feels like
a sharp knife in my belly.

236
00:10:08,941 --> 00:10:12,676
[ Groans, Screams ]

237
00:10:12,678 --> 00:10:13,978
[ Groaning ]

238
00:10:13,980 --> 00:10:16,947
[ Whispering ]
Psst! Gene. Hey.

239
00:10:16,949 --> 00:10:18,816
[ Groaning Continues ]

240
00:10:18,818 --> 00:10:20,384
Gene. Gene.

241
00:10:20,386 --> 00:10:21,952
Yeah? Uh-huh?

242
00:10:21,954 --> 00:10:23,120
Are you done?
No.

243
00:10:23,122 --> 00:10:24,421
I need you to serve this
to table 3.

244
00:10:24,423 --> 00:10:27,358
[ Linda ] Bob, shh!
He's dying. Stop.
I'm sorry.

245
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,759
Come on--
[ Clears Throat ]

246
00:10:28,761 --> 00:10:33,097
Come on, butler.
Let's go out
into the garden.

247
00:10:33,099 --> 00:10:34,865
Uhh--

248
00:10:34,867 --> 00:10:37,701
Tina! Tina,
it's your big line.

249
00:10:37,703 --> 00:10:39,036
Uhh--

250
00:10:39,038 --> 00:10:40,971
- Go!
- No. Don't.

251
00:10:40,973 --> 00:10:43,907
The tree!
It's been murdered.

252
00:10:43,909 --> 00:10:48,045
Oh, butler,
who is committing
all these murders?

253
00:10:48,047 --> 00:10:50,347
Beats me.
Oh, there's my knife.

254
00:10:50,349 --> 00:10:52,716
Well, I sure don't know
whodunit.

255
00:10:52,718 --> 00:10:53,951
Do you?
♪ [ Keyboard ]

256
00:10:53,953 --> 00:10:56,220
Is the tree the murderer?
♪ [ Continues ]

257
00:10:56,222 --> 00:10:59,857
Or is the flower
delivery man the murderer?

258
00:10:59,859 --> 00:11:03,661
Or perhaps
the suspicious butler?

259
00:11:04,863 --> 00:11:06,463
Well, you're all wrong.

260
00:11:06,465 --> 00:11:09,033
♪ The murderer was me

261
00:11:09,035 --> 00:11:10,200
[ Keyboard: Bark ]
Ha, ha!

262
00:11:10,202 --> 00:11:11,769
What?
You explicitly told us...

263
00:11:11,771 --> 00:11:14,872
at the beginning of the show
you weren't the murderer.

264
00:11:14,874 --> 00:11:16,774
That's right.
It's a twist!

265
00:11:16,776 --> 00:11:20,277
No, it's a lie.
A lie is not a twist.

266
00:11:20,545 --> 00:11:23,113
Don't be nervous.
You do this all the time.

267
00:11:23,115 --> 00:11:27,451
The cast will be signing
autographs if anyone
would like one.

268
00:11:27,453 --> 00:11:29,253
Everyone back in their seat!
Now!

269
00:11:29,255 --> 00:11:30,988
This is a robbery!
♪ [ Suspense Note ]

270
00:11:30,990 --> 00:11:33,223
[ Woman ] Ooh.
A robbery--
Now that's a twist.

271
00:11:33,225 --> 00:11:37,094
This is not part
of the show, people.
This is a real robbery.

272
00:11:37,096 --> 00:11:37,961
Kids, get behind
the counter.

273
00:11:37,963 --> 00:11:41,298
[ Whispering ]
We can take this guy.
I go high, you go low.

274
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:43,434
Wait. What?
Never mind.
Never mind.

275
00:11:43,436 --> 00:11:45,169
Wait--
You blew it.
You blew it, Tina.

276
00:11:45,171 --> 00:11:48,806
Everyone stay where you are!
Give me everything
in the register.

277
00:11:48,808 --> 00:11:50,407
Yeah, fine. Listen.
There are kids here,

278
00:11:50,409 --> 00:11:54,845
so don't do
anything stupid...er
than rob this place.

279
00:11:54,847 --> 00:11:55,479
Shut up, greaseball.

280
00:11:55,481 --> 00:11:57,715
Don't call me greaseball.
♪ [ Note ]

281
00:11:57,717 --> 00:11:58,816
Uh, mask face.

282
00:11:58,818 --> 00:12:01,251
[ Laughter ]
It's not part of the show.

283
00:12:01,253 --> 00:12:03,821
- Show?
- ♪ [ Continues ]

284
00:12:04,022 --> 00:12:06,857
- Gene, stop.
- Just take it easy.

285
00:12:06,859 --> 00:12:09,126
Oh, I'll take it...
easy.
[ Crowd Murmurs ]

286
00:12:09,128 --> 00:12:12,930
[ Police Radio Chatter ]
Hmm! They added a robbery
element to the show.

287
00:12:12,932 --> 00:12:15,532
That's clever.
The ski mask
is a little cheesy.

288
00:12:15,534 --> 00:12:17,201
I think it looks
pretty good.

289
00:12:17,203 --> 00:12:18,335
Okay, that's all of it.

290
00:12:18,337 --> 00:12:20,504
You've got your money.
Now be on your way.

291
00:12:20,506 --> 00:12:23,273
- Give me a little music.
- Oh, come on. Just go.

292
00:12:23,275 --> 00:12:26,009
♪ [ Scatting ]
♪ [ Keyboard ]

293
00:12:26,011 --> 00:12:29,980
[ Scatting ]
Do your last line again.
Go!

294
00:12:30,248 --> 00:12:34,351
[ Flatly ]
You've got your money.
Now be on your way?

295
00:12:34,353 --> 00:12:36,353
♪ Maybe I'll leave

296
00:12:36,355 --> 00:12:39,389
♪ And maybe I'll stay

297
00:12:39,391 --> 00:12:42,392
♪ Maybe it's the limelight
♪ [ Keyboard Continues ]

298
00:12:42,394 --> 00:12:44,528
♪ Could be the singin'

299
00:12:44,530 --> 00:12:49,366
♪ 911 should be a-ringin'

300
00:12:49,368 --> 00:12:51,869
♪ But I can't stop

301
00:12:51,871 --> 00:12:56,406
♪ And neither can I

302
00:12:56,408 --> 00:12:58,575
Sit down, sit down!

303
00:12:58,577 --> 00:13:02,246
I'm kidding. I'm kid--
Everyone up. Come on!

304
00:13:02,248 --> 00:13:05,149
It's not part
of the show.

305
00:13:05,151 --> 00:13:05,983
Play me out.

306
00:13:05,985 --> 00:13:09,486
♪ [ Bouncy ]
[ Applause Continues ]

307
00:13:09,821 --> 00:13:13,123
Can you break a five?
I'd love to tip out
the cast.

308
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:16,059
♪ [ Stops ]
No! I can't
break a five, lady!

309
00:13:16,061 --> 00:13:19,129
I was just robbed!
Did you not just see that?

310
00:13:19,131 --> 00:13:21,131
You were standing
right here, idiot!

311
00:13:21,133 --> 00:13:24,835
Oh, you people commit.
Get out!

312
00:13:26,604 --> 00:13:29,940
We feel terrible
we didn't stop that
robbery last night.

313
00:13:29,942 --> 00:13:32,576
Oh, that robbery
was horrible!
[ Shudders ]

314
00:13:32,578 --> 00:13:36,647
Though I have to admit,
it felt so good to hear
the audience applaud.

315
00:13:36,649 --> 00:13:41,485
- [ Bell Rings ]
- Hey, are you guys talking
about that show last night?

316
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:43,053
I thought it was dazzling.

317
00:13:43,055 --> 00:13:45,589
Oh, yeah?
You saw Dreamatorium?

318
00:13:45,591 --> 00:13:46,490
Yeah, I caught the end of it.

319
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:49,526
I thought the guy
who played the robber
really stole the show.

320
00:13:49,528 --> 00:13:50,961
Is that
why you guys are here?

321
00:13:50,963 --> 00:13:53,630
No, they're here because
the robber was a real robber...

322
00:13:53,632 --> 00:13:55,165
and he stole 227 bucks.

323
00:13:55,167 --> 00:13:58,302
- Eh, a little less than that.
- It'll be hard to catch
this guy.

324
00:13:58,304 --> 00:14:00,037
Nobody got
a good look at him.

325
00:14:00,039 --> 00:14:01,872
Put this down
in your report.

326
00:14:01,874 --> 00:14:04,074
He was leading-man handsome.

327
00:14:04,076 --> 00:14:05,108
He was wearing a ski mask.

328
00:14:05,110 --> 00:14:09,179
Well, he had the presence
of a young Burt Reynolds.

329
00:14:09,181 --> 00:14:11,582
And the pipes
of an old Debbie Reynolds.

330
00:14:11,584 --> 00:14:13,183
Hey, the online
reviews are in.

331
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:16,587
Listen to this one.
It's from whosyourdaddy1997.

332
00:14:16,589 --> 00:14:17,955
"The plot
made zero sense,

333
00:14:17,957 --> 00:14:19,389
and the set looked
like children
made it."

334
00:14:19,391 --> 00:14:22,492
Yeah!
Children did make it--
my children!

335
00:14:22,494 --> 00:14:28,031
"But the reason to go see
Dreamatorium is the
closing musical number.

336
00:14:28,033 --> 00:14:30,267
The chemistry between
the robber character...

337
00:14:30,269 --> 00:14:34,671
and the lonely morgue
operator was sparktastic."

338
00:14:34,673 --> 00:14:36,506
Did anyone
mention the food?

339
00:14:36,508 --> 00:14:38,208
Uh, no.

340
00:14:38,210 --> 00:14:40,711
Great. So the robbery
got rave reviews.

341
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:41,678
Bob, we're a hit!

342
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:44,214
- No, Linda. We were hit.
- Good one.

343
00:14:44,216 --> 00:14:45,782
Yeah.
That's good.
Thanks.

344
00:14:45,784 --> 00:14:47,517
- I don't get it.
- We were hit.

345
00:14:47,519 --> 00:14:50,320
A hit is a ro--
Am I wrong?
It's a robbery, right?

346
00:14:50,322 --> 00:14:52,222
- [ Chattering ]
- Right. A hit is a robbery.

347
00:14:52,224 --> 00:14:53,423
Well, technically,
for the cops--

348
00:14:53,425 --> 00:14:55,158
Technically, no,
it's not--
Wait--

349
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:56,593
- Forget it. Forget it.
- In layman--

350
00:14:56,595 --> 00:14:58,428
In layman's terms.
Forget it. Everybody.

351
00:14:58,430 --> 00:15:00,964
Nobody got hit.
Everybody, forget it.

352
00:15:01,666 --> 00:15:04,635
There we were, putting on
the show of our lives,

353
00:15:04,637 --> 00:15:07,604
when in walked a man
with a gun in his hand.

354
00:15:07,606 --> 00:15:09,339
And he was looking
for you-know-who.

355
00:15:09,341 --> 00:15:12,976
- We will now take questions.
- Here, here, here!

356
00:15:12,978 --> 00:15:14,144
- Me.
- Large Tommy.

357
00:15:14,146 --> 00:15:16,380
Question for Tina.
Were you scared?

358
00:15:16,382 --> 00:15:20,150
Um, uh--
Uhh--

359
00:15:20,152 --> 00:15:20,984
No, she wasn't.

360
00:15:20,986 --> 00:15:22,686
- Ooh! Ooh!
- Normal-size Jenny.

361
00:15:22,688 --> 00:15:25,555
How big was the gun,
and did anyone get shot?

362
00:15:25,557 --> 00:15:28,725
That's a two-part question.
I don't answer those.

363
00:15:28,727 --> 00:15:29,960
- Aw.
- Tiny Peter.

364
00:15:29,962 --> 00:15:31,695
Does this mean
you're in a gang now?

365
00:15:31,697 --> 00:15:35,666
That is correct.
Our gang is called
the Broken Glass Kids.

366
00:15:35,668 --> 00:15:38,135
- We'll cut you.
- [ Gasping ]

367
00:15:38,137 --> 00:15:38,468
Wow!

368
00:15:38,470 --> 00:15:41,271
[ Linda ]
Oh! I can't wait
for the show tonight.

369
00:15:41,273 --> 00:15:41,672
What, tonight?

370
00:15:41,674 --> 00:15:43,740
I thought maybe you'd
consider canceling,

371
00:15:43,742 --> 00:15:47,110
but you're really committed
to making me unhappy.

372
00:15:47,112 --> 00:15:50,147
The show won't be the same
without the robber.

373
00:15:50,149 --> 00:15:52,416
What?
You're all thinking it!

374
00:15:52,418 --> 00:15:57,387
I got to agree.
That guy could really
sing... and rob.

375
00:15:57,389 --> 00:15:58,689
Well, again, our apologies.

376
00:15:58,691 --> 00:16:01,191
We'll follow up as soon
as we hear anything.

377
00:16:01,193 --> 00:16:02,960
So happy for you though.

378
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:04,094
Thanks.

379
00:16:04,096 --> 00:16:05,362
[ Sighs ]
Mort.

380
00:16:05,364 --> 00:16:06,330
[ Bell Dings ]
You're right.

381
00:16:06,332 --> 00:16:08,565
What am I gonna do
without the robber?

382
00:16:08,567 --> 00:16:10,534
You'll just have to--

383
00:16:10,536 --> 00:16:15,238
♪ Take it easy

384
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:17,374
Wait a minute.
That voice.

385
00:16:17,376 --> 00:16:20,610
Oh, my God! It's you!
You're the robber!

386
00:16:20,612 --> 00:16:21,712
Guilty.
[ Exclaims ]

387
00:16:21,714 --> 00:16:23,447
Last night was something,
wasn't it?

388
00:16:23,449 --> 00:16:26,183
Oh, I know.
We were electric together.

389
00:16:26,185 --> 00:16:28,085
So let's do it again tonight.

390
00:16:28,087 --> 00:16:29,052
Yes.
I want to report a, uh--

391
00:16:29,054 --> 00:16:32,389
What are you doing, Linda?
I'm getting this guy arrested.
[ Dialing ]

392
00:16:32,391 --> 00:16:34,391
No, but he wants
to do the show again.

393
00:16:34,393 --> 00:16:37,127
[ Grunting ]
He robbed us with a gun.
[ Stammers ]

394
00:16:37,129 --> 00:16:39,463
Hey, everyone, relax.
It wasn't even a real gun.

395
00:16:39,465 --> 00:16:44,267
Fake. And currently
in my other jacket locked
in the trunk of my car.

396
00:16:44,269 --> 00:16:45,202
Bob, he wants to perform.

397
00:16:45,204 --> 00:16:49,606
This guy is the missing
ingredient to my show.
He's my garlic powder.

398
00:16:49,608 --> 00:16:52,676
Yes. The man who robbed
my restaurant
is here right now.

399
00:16:52,678 --> 00:16:55,112
He's about 5'8",
maybe 150 pounds.

400
00:16:55,114 --> 00:16:57,247
I'm bad at guessing weight
though, so--

401
00:16:57,249 --> 00:16:58,782
Yeah, I'll say.
Yeah.

402
00:16:58,784 --> 00:17:01,485
Uh-- 160?
Oh, flatterer.

403
00:17:01,487 --> 00:17:03,120
All right, 170.

404
00:17:03,122 --> 00:17:03,754
Ooh!
[ Yelps ]

405
00:17:03,756 --> 00:17:06,390
Uh, call you back.
You said the gun
was in your car.

406
00:17:06,392 --> 00:17:09,059
- I lied.
- What about it being fake?

407
00:17:09,061 --> 00:17:09,659
Also a lie.

408
00:17:09,661 --> 00:17:12,162
See?
A lie can be a twist.

409
00:17:12,164 --> 00:17:16,333
Since you did that,
I'm gonna do this.
Register.

410
00:17:17,168 --> 00:17:18,368
Great. Again.

411
00:17:18,370 --> 00:17:20,704
Good luck tonight without me!

412
00:17:20,706 --> 00:17:22,339
We forgot to give this
to you.

413
00:17:22,341 --> 00:17:24,441
A little
"Sorry we let the robber
get away" Bundt cake.

414
00:17:24,443 --> 00:17:26,710
You're doing it again.
He just ran right past you.
[ Radio Chatter ]

415
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:30,847
Hold that thought, Bob.
The guy who robbed us
just robbed us again!

416
00:17:30,849 --> 00:17:32,482
Hold on. Can you
repeat that, Dispatch?

417
00:17:32,484 --> 00:17:34,584
Suspect--
[ Continues, Indistinct ]
He's saying what I'm saying.

418
00:17:34,586 --> 00:17:36,219
The guy who robbed us--
he just left.

419
00:17:36,221 --> 00:17:41,058
We got to go, Bob.
The guy who robbed you
was just spotted in the area!

420
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:43,627
[ Bell Rings ]

421
00:17:46,330 --> 00:17:48,665
[ Panting ]

422
00:17:49,233 --> 00:17:50,667
Don't catch him,
don't catch him,

423
00:17:50,669 --> 00:17:52,436
don't catch him,
don't catch him!

424
00:17:52,438 --> 00:17:53,270
[ Grunts ]

425
00:17:53,272 --> 00:17:55,105
Ah, they got him.

426
00:17:55,273 --> 00:17:57,374
Geez.
Julia packs a wallop.

427
00:17:57,376 --> 00:18:00,277
Ah, you couldn't just let me
have my dream, could you?

428
00:18:00,279 --> 00:18:02,779
What? You mean 'cause
I called the police?

429
00:18:02,781 --> 00:18:05,248
The guy committed
armed robbery, Lin-- twice.

430
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:09,386
But you committed murder, Bob.
You blew my dream's head off.

431
00:18:09,388 --> 00:18:10,854
That's a little
dramatic, Lin.

432
00:18:10,856 --> 00:18:15,759
Yes, Bob, 'cause I used
to be an actor.

433
00:18:18,796 --> 00:18:21,331
Only two tickets left
for Dreamatorium,

434
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:25,235
the show over three people
have been blogging about.

435
00:18:25,237 --> 00:18:26,803
Final performance, people.

436
00:18:26,805 --> 00:18:29,706
Do you think you're gonna
say your line tonight?

437
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:30,307
Probably not.

438
00:18:30,309 --> 00:18:32,709
You know, a good way to
beat the stage fright--

439
00:18:32,711 --> 00:18:34,878
imagine
the audience naked.

440
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:38,181
I already do that.
I imagine everyone naked.

441
00:18:38,183 --> 00:18:39,850
Everyone?
All the time?

442
00:18:39,852 --> 00:18:42,419
Yeah. You don't do that?

443
00:18:42,421 --> 00:18:43,019
No.
Oh.

444
00:18:43,021 --> 00:18:46,890
Well, try
picturing the audience
with clothes on then.

445
00:18:46,892 --> 00:18:48,391
Like all their clothes?

446
00:18:48,393 --> 00:18:52,229
Well, maybe just
a condom and a hat.

447
00:18:52,231 --> 00:18:52,863
Okay.

448
00:18:52,865 --> 00:18:56,633
Tonight's show is
officially sold out.
Packed house.

449
00:18:56,635 --> 00:18:59,469
Are you feeling it, Mom?
Whoo!

450
00:18:59,471 --> 00:19:02,239
Are you feeling it, Dad?
Whoo!

451
00:19:02,241 --> 00:19:03,473
Eh, who cares?

452
00:19:03,475 --> 00:19:05,609
The audience is expecting
to be dazzled,

453
00:19:05,611 --> 00:19:07,711
but thanks to your father,
we have no star.

454
00:19:07,713 --> 00:19:11,815
[ Sighs ]
Let's just go do the version
everyone hated.

455
00:19:11,817 --> 00:19:12,449
Whodunit?

456
00:19:12,451 --> 00:19:15,852
Was the murderer
the corpse delivery guy?
♪ [ Keyboard ]

457
00:19:15,854 --> 00:19:19,422
Or was it
the flower delivery guy?

458
00:19:19,424 --> 00:19:22,826
Or was the murderer
the shifty butler?

459
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:23,727
♪ [ Continues ]
Wrong.

460
00:19:23,729 --> 00:19:26,496
The murderer was me.
Thank you. Good night.

461
00:19:26,498 --> 00:19:27,964
Hold on. I saw
the show last night.

462
00:19:27,966 --> 00:19:29,432
Trust me,
it's about to get good.

463
00:19:29,434 --> 00:19:32,302
That's our show, everyone.
Thanks for coming out.

464
00:19:32,304 --> 00:19:34,638
What about the you-know-who
surprise performer?

465
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:38,508
Yeah, well, the show is
what it is, so-- Good night.

466
00:19:38,510 --> 00:19:41,211
I'll tell you what it is.
It's garbage.

467
00:19:44,615 --> 00:19:47,317
Okay, all right then.
Drive safe.

468
00:19:47,319 --> 00:19:49,619
[ Bob ]
Nobody move!
This is a robbery!

469
00:19:49,621 --> 00:19:52,789
I said sit back down,
lady, or I'll shoot!

470
00:19:52,791 --> 00:19:55,458
Oh, Bobby,
you're in the show!

471
00:19:55,460 --> 00:19:56,560
Garbage.
I don't want your money.

472
00:19:56,562 --> 00:20:00,864
I just want the money
of the big shot
who owns this place.

473
00:20:00,866 --> 00:20:03,233
Ooh, way to commit, honey.

474
00:20:03,935 --> 00:20:05,535
Boy, I thought
we did better today.

475
00:20:05,537 --> 00:20:09,072
Oh. Well--
[ Clears Throat ]
All right, here it goes.

476
00:20:09,074 --> 00:20:16,079
♪ So I'm singin' words
to a song
I'm making up right now ♪

477
00:20:16,081 --> 00:20:20,784
♪ 'Cause it's
the singing that matters
and not the song ♪

478
00:20:20,786 --> 00:20:23,320
♪ So it's up to me

479
00:20:23,322 --> 00:20:24,754
♪ To
♪ Sing

480
00:20:24,756 --> 00:20:27,857
♪ In
[ High-pitched ]
♪ Key

481
00:20:27,859 --> 00:20:28,458
Ow!
Ow!

482
00:20:28,460 --> 00:20:30,860
[ Both, Out of Tune ]
♪ Key

483
00:20:30,862 --> 00:20:32,329
♪ Ee
♪ Ee

484
00:20:32,331 --> 00:20:33,430
That was great.

485
00:20:33,432 --> 00:20:34,998
Yeah, just go--
[ Laughs ]
What? I--

486
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,833
It's a little high.
Well, I nailed it.

487
00:20:36,835 --> 00:20:39,469
You were a little high.
So you go higher.

488
00:20:39,471 --> 00:20:40,337
Oh.
I think we can--

489
00:20:40,339 --> 00:20:41,972
Everyone's gone.
Yeah, I think
we can stop.

490
00:20:41,974 --> 00:20:44,941
- We cleared them out.
- No. Don't.

491
00:20:44,943 --> 00:20:48,678
I did it.
Tina, take a bow, girl.

